The paper presents a technique for generating Magnetic Resonance Angiography (MRA) images from existing T1-weighted and T2-weighted MRI images using a generative adversarial network (GAN). This involves image synthesis and computer vision, which are subfields of computer science that fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
